Introduction {#s1}
============

*Trypanosoma brucei* is an extracellular human pathogen with an unparalleled capacity to evade host humoral immunity. The causative agent of African sleeping sickness in humans and nagana in cattle, *T. brucei* is transmitted into the bloodstream of its host by a tsetse vector and can grow to densities as high as 10^9^ cells per milliliter of blood. The parasitemia is cyclically diminished to nearly undetectable levels, to be followed by another wave of immense growth [@ppat.1002900-Barry1]. These rounds of parasitemia reflect the battle between the host immune system and the pathogen\'s elegant mechanisms of immune evasion.

